author: ias
msg: testComprehensiveTypes uses StringBuffer instead of simple concatenation.
Sun's JDK 1.4.2 (both _01 and _02) can't compile WSDLTest.java with a message that the result of the concatenation is too long for a String constant.
(According to Dr. Kim, one of my colleagues and specialized in JVM, told me a String constant in a class binary has the limit of 64k.)
I also think that dealing with (extremely) long String instances, it's better to use a StringBuffer usually for better performance and stability.
